  I'll just say that I'm rather less than comfortable with the increasing
use of "pseudo-domains."  I'm very much in favor of the domain system and
feel really quite strongly that current users of the ".uucp" pseudo-domain
should be strongly urged to migrate into the real domain *.&lt;state abbrev&gt;.US

  In similar fashion, mightn't BITNET consider a solution like UU.NET has
provided for UUCP --  i.e. register an official domain *.BIT.NET or some
such ??

  These aren't religious positions on my part, but are intended as food for
thought by the folks who actually resolve these net issues ( != myself
in any event.)

   Ran
